__NAME__ purpose
parse (interpolate) variable values before storing them
__END__


__NAME__ synopsis
<group choice='plain'>
	<arg choice='plain'>No</arg>
	<arg choice='plain'>Yes</arg>
</group>
__END__


__NAME__ description
Specify that the &glos-configuration; directives should have their 
values parsed (&glos-interpolate;d).
</para><para>
This applies to all configuration directives except &conf-Variable;.
</para><para>
Of variables, only those in ALL CAPS are interpolated.
__END__

__NAME__ example: Enabling ParseVariables globally
<programlisting>
ParseVariables 1
</programlisting>
__END__

__NAME__ example: Defining a variable containing parse-needing data
<programlisting>
Variable STORE_ID topshop

ParseVariables Yes
StaticDir  /home/__STORE_ID__/www/cat
ParseVariables No
</programlisting>
__END__

